12.17.22 ~ “and I would tell you what an awakening it was to love you.” 🌹 @chloefrayne 

4 years. Four long years since we told you we loved you and kissed you goodnight for the last time, Claire. 😭💔

When you are the parent of a child with a terminal prognosis, it can be damn near impossible to juggle the paralyzing fear, the sadness that you will likely outlive your child, and also the limitless joy of every single moment you have together. We were petrified that every single sniffle was the “beginning of the end.” I am not sure I took a full, deep breath the entire first year of your life. I just wanted TIME. I begged the heavens for it nightly. I kept hearing that asshole doctor’s words echoing in my head… “Claire likely won’t live to age 1…” and deep down, I was terrified he may be right. 

I think it was sometime during the second year of your life that I finally listened to the real expert on your life — YOU. I finally realized that no book, no expert, no fancy publication or research study could ever predetermine length of life, let alone take into account a child’s will to live. And it would be no surprise to us or anyone who knew you that you defied those odds by giving us roughly 16 “extra” years more than was predicted for you. That’s just who you were, Mimi. 

(Continued in comments… 👇🏼)
Merry Christmas from us to you! 💗🌵💗

1.22.23 ~ Gigi, wearing her sisters’ hats & scarf… 🥹 (Her mood on the Yoda hat!!!! 😂🤣)

(Gi was born one week to the day after Lola died. 💗) xo

"Sometimes I miss you the way someone drowning remembers the air.” ~Tim Seibles

8.10.07 ~ Oh, sweet Lola… We will love you 4ever and ever and beyond, baby girl. 💗♾️

We simply cannot wrap our minds around the fact that your 17th birthday is next week. How can this even be?! How do we celebrate and honor your life without you here, now our 4th birthday without you earthside? How is the human heart able to handle all this longing and aching without shattering? How will life ever make sense again without you & your sister here? Do you have any idea how much we love you — how our love just keeps growing infinitely and exponentially each day we are apart? Where do I put all this overflowing love and emotion now? 

You were worth it all, Mrs. Pockey, and then some. I miss you and love you so very much… ✨

4.28.23 ~ Happy 17th Birthday, Lola. Today we celebrate your 4th birthday in heaven. Oh, how we miss your tiny, strong body, your sly grins, your flowing, curly locks, & your petite hands with thumbs tucked inside. We miss your freckles, your not-so-subtle vocal protests, your curious eyes meeting ours every time we enter the room, & seeing you intertwined with your loyal doggy, Cash. We miss watching you eat & drink bottles like a pro, pull your feet up super fast when they touched water you considered cold (under 90°F 😂), watch “Dresses” (Say Yes to the Dress) & Little People, Big World on TV, and carefully hold your beloved Bok. Your life was so full, Mrs. Pock. 

You truly lived, loved, and experienced the world around you… and thankfully, the world got the privilege of being witness to your extraordinary life for 13.5 years, too. How lucky we all are for this… for you… for the gift of your one, precious life. ✨

This grief is brutal, never-ending, relentless. It obliterated us then, and it continues to do so now. I sometimes wonder if our pain is there to serve as a reminder of just how intensely & completely we have loved you — and continue to love you — in light of your absence. Looking back through old pictures is almost more than I can handle, remembering being alive together and filled with such gratitude. Those palpable images of true happiness warm my heart but also make me long deeply for what we once had.  What I wouldn’t give to see you curled up asleep in Cal’s arms again or bouncing around like a silly, tiny ninja with your Daddy. I often close my eyes and picture you cuddled into my left arm in your favorite spot, head on my heart, your breathing synchronized with mine. I think I will always go to this special place when my heart feels lost and separate from yours because it brings me right back to you, baby girl. I love you so. Forever and ever, Pockey. Happy Birthday, my love. 🪽🤍

5.24.23 ~ “I listened closely today and I swear to you that my heartbeat, in perfect Morse Code, was slowly and efficiently typing out your name.” ~ @tylerknott 

Happy Anniversary, babe. I am so damn lucky to get to do life with you. 💗♾️

6.18.23 ~ Happy Father’s Day to the best dad I have ever had the privilege of knowing. You are our rock, Scott… you always have been. We love you so very much for always, babe. #foreverafamilyof5 

(I cannot tell you how sad it will forever be to me that I have to dig back through my old pictures to find shots of Claire & Lola with their Daddy… no “new” pictures to post. Today my heart goes out to all the fathers who have lost children… I am so sorry that this day will forever hold a very different meaning to you after suffering such great loss. All my love to you on this day. 💔💗)

Circa late 1900’s. 😅 ~ Our engagement pics from back in the day… And yes, we did take them with our first child, Halley (whose birthday is ironically today)! 😂 I guess it’s a good thing that this just seems like maybe 10-15 years ago, right?! Love you so much, babe! 💗♾️

PS — We look 16 and whyyyy the hell did I wear a turtleneck of all things and not show the ring and also use this Josten’s marbled background FFS. 🤣🤦🏼‍♀️

“i will never be finished loving you 
in this lifetime,
or in any lifetime.” 💗♾️ @wilderpoetry 

7.22.23 ~ Happy Birthday, Scott! Of one thing I am sure, this adventure we call life has been so much better because you’re a part of it. You have my heart for always! Love you so, so much, babe! 💋

7.25.23 ~ Happy 22nd Birthday, Claire❣️😭 I have no words. Just absolutely none at all. I wish I could be with you today and celebrate you like I always planned we would. I miss you infinitely and love you with everything in me, Mimi. Thank you for being my daughter in this life, boo. I could not have been luckier. 🌙💗

PS ~ Trying to imagine what you would be like at age 22, and this first picture makes me smile to think of you this way... happy and free. 🌼 (Pic with silly filter was taken 10.14.18, just two months before Claire’s passing.)

social_posts.post_text: “My footsteps know the mountain, a rhythm born from soul.” ⛰️💗 @angieweilandcrosby

10.12.23 ~ Four years. How can this be??? We miss you every moment of every day, Lola. I miss your feistiness & drama, seeing Bok inside your cute little hands, the way your body nestled into mine like it was just supposed to be there all my life. I miss braiding your hair while you held so still, zooming you in your walker, watching you & Cashy cuddle, seeing you and Claire “fight” then love on each other, and seeing the world through your eyes and experiences. I miss being your mommy in this life. Thank you for sending SO many tree frogs and angels and feathers. We have felt you with us so much these past few months in all the new places and happy moments. We talk about you all the time and remember our love, as it permeates through every moment of every single day. So fucking grateful to be your Mommy forever and ever, baby girl. What I wouldn’t give for just one more cuddle, one more smooch, one more minute with you, Miss Pock. I carry you inside my heart forever, my baby. It truly could be no other way. I love you to the stars and beyond, Pockey. Meet me there tonight in my dreams. ✨🐥💛

12.1.23 ~ “I loved you then and I love you now and I have loved you every second in between.” ~Stephen King 💞

Happy 25th Birthday, Cal!!! 🥳💗 Cannot believe it’s been a quarter of a century since you first made me a mama❣️It has been my absolute privilege getting to watch the man you’ve become — I could not be prouder of you if I tried. You’re forever my heart… I love you so. Xoxo

12.17.23 ~ 5 years. It’s simply unfathomable, Claire. It is unfathomable in every way how we have survived this long without you… how the sun and moon have continued rising and setting… how all of life has simply “gone on” in the absence of such an important person. I don’t want to keep doing this year after year — trying to find the perfect words which are adequate enough to sum up just how much you altered the very course of my life & everyone’s lives around you and then how soul-shattering it was for all of us to have to say goodbye. 😭💔

17 years was so much longer than we were ever told we would get with you, but they also were not even close to enough. I miss you, Claire. The whole world misses your serene, gentle being and those great big soulful eyes of yours. You were everything. Always. 🐞

This song played on a random shuffle yesterday when I was thinking of you and I instantly felt you with me… Just like I did when I found the tiny white feather and saw the rainbow prism by your picture today. I know you’re here… you’re absolutely present in all of these moments & more. Because of course you are. I am finding gratitude for these precious moments — but they will never replace how good it felt to hug you, to see your grin light up the room, to be in your physical presence. You changed people. You changed me. I am so very grateful for always. I love you, Mimi. 🌙 #moonofmylife

∞ @infinityartglass
